        }, 
        {
            "abbrName": "cog", 
            "eName": "Cognizer", 
            "isMapped": false, 
            "cName": null, 
            "isCore": true, 
            "def": "The Cognizer is the person whose Opinion is in question. \n\nMy take is that Johnson will not actually make it to the last round .\nEveryone is entitled to their opinion ."
        }, 
        {
            "abbrName": "opi", 
            "eName": "Opinion", 
            "isMapped": false, 
            "cName": null, 
            "isCore": true, 
            "def": "The Cognizer's way of thinking, which is not necessarily generally accepted, and which is generally dependent on the Cognizer's point of view.\n\nMy take is that it is a version of the Macbeth story - what happens when people\nbecome violent but cannot quite handle it.\nSvetlana knew that it was Sergei's view that the Berlin crises were merely a charade which it was necessary for both sides to enact and re-enact every few years.\nHer child-like portrayal only manages to live up to the other characters' view of her as the deranged little sister.\n"
        }, 
        {
            "abbrName": "evi", 
            "eName": "Evidence", 
            "isMapped": false, 
            "cName": null, 
            "isCore": false, 
            "def": "The events or states-of-affairs that form the basis for the Cognizer's Opinion.\n\nFrom what I've seen so far, my opinion is that it won't really matter.\n"
        }, 
        {
            "abbrName": "con", 
            "eName": "Constancy", 
            "isMapped": false, 
            "cName": null, 
            "isCore": false, 
            "def": "The level of firmness with which the Cognizer holds an opinion.  It refers to the amount of convincing that they would need to change their mind.\n\nI really think that you should reconsider. "
        }, 
        {
            "abbrName": "dom", 
            "eName": "Domain", 
            "isMapped": false, 
            "cName": null, 
            "isCore": false, 
            "def": "The aspects of the Opinion (and its Topic, if any) which are under consideration.\n\nWe seemed to have two quite different moral views about this situation.\nNoone could take seriously Dr. Furst's ill-advised medical opinion that Terry was still alive."
        }, 
        {
            "abbrName": null, 
